description:
You&#39;ll be something of a dandy when donning this dapper suit from the 40s! It&#39;s a wonderful wool tweed fabric in grey, black, red and white in such fine stripes that an optical illusion of pink and gray pinstripes is created! The double breasted jacket features three external pockets, one interior pocket, butterfly lining and gray marbleized buttons. The pleated front trousers feature dropped belt loops, suspender buttons, side slash pockets, welted back pockets, wallet button, cuffed legs and metal Talon zipper with single gripper snap for closure. By &quot;Arbitman&#39;s&quot; and featuring a 1939--1949 Union Label that dates this suit to the 1940s. This suit is in great vintage condition, with a few well done period mends, but no stains, holes, nor odors to note. 

Please Note: We list the Suit Size in the Title. A &quot;Suit Size&quot; is taken from your actual chest measurement. While we&#39;d like a well-fitted suit, we don&#39;t want a skin-tight suit, so the actual jacket chest measurement is generally a few inches larger.

